The paper deals with unsupervised domain translation and weakly supervised segmentation, which are both topics in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves disentangling the common and separate parts of the domains, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a mask to focus attention on desired augmentation is a technique used in multimedia (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely to be relevant to this paper.
